      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The civil rights movement in the US was a pivotal moment in American history, marked by a series of courageous actions and landmark legislation. It began with the Montgomery Bus Boycott (1955-1956), led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., where African Americans fought against segregation on public buses. The movement gained momentum with the March on Washington (1963), where King delivered his iconic \"I Have a Dream\" speech, and the passage of the Civil Rights Act (1964) and Voting Rights Act (1965), which outlawed segregation and protected voting rights. The movement continued with the Selma to Montgomery Marches (1965) and the assassinations of prominent leaders, including Martin Luther King Jr. in 1968.",
